 foxtrotting among gleaming white tables on the bright-lit floor of a café. The orchestra was playing and gasping for breath. There was among the dancers a tall American Negro who smiled tolerantly as one passionate pair bumped into him and his blonde partner.

“We’ll find it, we must find it,” continued Martha in a rapid patter in time to the music; “after all, we are within our rights.”

